title: Were Most Jobs Added in February 2021 ‘Waiters and Bartenders’?
subtitle: Some online observers critical of U.S. President Joe Biden sought to undercut a broadly positive employment update in March 2021.
author: Dan MacGuill
vclaim: Around three-quarters of the 379,000 jobs added to the U.S. economy in February 2021 were made up of "waiters and bartenders."
